cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for click-through rate (CTR) prediction, which is a common task in recommendation systems. The framework introduces time information to track the evolution of user interests, which is a key aspect of CTR prediction. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
